StatCrunch Chapter 2

Working with Team Batting Data

To illustrate the construction of several graphs and summaries for a single batch of data, I read in the 2015 team batting data stored in the StatCrunch file TSUB case 2.1.

Stemplot

Suppose I want to construct a stemplot of the number of triples of all teams.

I open up the Graph menu:

If I select the Stem and Leaf option, I see the following window. I select the variable 3B and then select Calculate.

I see a stemplot where the leaf value is the ones place.

Other Plots (dotplot and histogram)

We can construct alternative displays by other choices from the Graph menu.

Here I choose the dotplot option and the variable 3B to get a dotplot of these team triple counts.

Or I might perfer a histogram choose Histogram from the main menu.

Summaries

If we want to compute summaries, say a five-number summary, of the triple counts, then we choose Summary Stats from the Stat menu.

By choosing the Summary Stats -> Columns, and then choosing the variable 3B, then we get a collection of different summary statistics for triples include the five number summary(Min, Q1, Median, Q3, Max).
